node.text:
@hypeart: "L’Arc de Triomphe Wrapped," the brain-child of the late artist couple Christo and Jeanne-Claude, has been 60 years in the making, and it is finally ready. “Like classical sculpture, all our wrapped projects are not solid buildings; they are moving with the wind, they are breathing,” Christo mentioned in an interview before his unfortunate passing last year. “The fabric is very sensual and inviting; it’s like a skin.” Hit the link in bio to explore the significance behind this momentous project. ⁠
Photo: @karlhab
